.PP

.B === 
.B Stream builders
.B 
.B 
.B    Warning: these functions create streams with fast access; it is illegal
.B    to mix them with streams built with [< >]; would raise Failure
.B    when accessing such mixed streams\&. ===

.PP

.I val from 
: 
.B (int -> 'a option) -> 'a t
.sp

.B Stream\&.from f
returns a stream built from the function 
.B f
\&.
To create a new stream element, the function 
.B f
is called with
the current stream count\&. The user function 
.B f
must return either
.B Some <value>
for a value or 
.B None
to specify the end of the
stream\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val of_list 
: 
.B 'a list -> 'a t
.sp
Return the stream holding the elements of the list in the same
order\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val of_string 
: 
.B string -> char t
.sp
Return the stream of the characters of the string parameter\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val of_channel 
: 
.B Pervasives.in_channel -> char t
.sp
Return the stream of the characters read from the input channel\&.
.sp

.sp

.PP

.B === 
.B Stream iterator
.B  ===

.PP

.I val iter 
: 
.B ('a -> unit) -> 'a t -> unit
.sp

.B Stream\&.iter f s
scans the whole stream s, applying function 
.B f
in turn to each stream element encountered\&.
.sp

.sp

.PP

.B === 
.B Predefined parsers
.B  ===

.PP

.I val next 
: 
.B 'a t -> 'a
.sp
Return the first element of the stream and remove it from the
stream\&. Raise Stream\&.Failure if the stream is empty\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val empty 
: 
.B 'a t -> unit
.sp
Return 
.B ()
if the stream is empty, else raise 
.B Stream\&.Failure
\&.
.sp

.sp

.PP

.B === 
.B Useful functions
.B  ===

.PP

.I val peek 
: 
.B 'a t -> 'a option
.sp
Return 
.B Some
of "the first element" of the stream, or 
.B None
if
the stream is empty\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val junk 
: 
.B 'a t -> unit
.sp
Remove the first element of the stream, possibly unfreezing
it before\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val count 
: 
.B 'a t -> int
.sp
Return the current count of the stream elements, i\&.e\&. the number
of the stream elements discarded\&.
.sp

.sp

.I val npeek 
: 
.B int -> 'a t -> 'a list
.sp

.B npeek n
returns the list of the 
.B n
first elements of
the stream, or all its remaining elements if less than 
.B n
elements are available\&.
.sp

